<item>
            <title>[DERBY-6602] LuceneQueryVTI handles NULL key values inconsistently</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-6602</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If there&apos;s an integer key column with a NULL value, the Lucene query will return a fake key value (0) rather than NULL. The document id and score will be correct. Example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;ij&amp;gt; create table t1(x int, c clob);
0 rows inserted/updated/deleted
ij&amp;gt; insert into t1 values (null, &apos;abc&apos;), (null, &apos;def&apos;);
2 rows inserted/updated/deleted
ij&amp;gt; call lucenesupport.createindex(&apos;app&apos;, &apos;t1&apos;, &apos;c&apos;, null, &apos;x&apos;);
0 rows inserted/updated/deleted
ij&amp;gt; select * from table(t1__c(&apos;abc or def&apos;, null, 3, null)) tc;
X          |DOCUMENTID |SCORE          
---------------------------------------
0          |0          |0.35355338     
0          |1          |0.35355338     

2 rows selected
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If the key column is a string type, the returned key is correct (NULL). The document id is sometimes correct and sometimes NULL, and the score seems to be NULL always. Example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;ij&amp;gt; create table t2(x varchar(10), c clob);
0 rows inserted/updated/deleted
ij&amp;gt; insert into t2 values (null, &apos;abc&apos;), (null, &apos;def&apos;);
2 rows inserted/updated/deleted
ij&amp;gt; call lucenesupport.createindex(&apos;app&apos;, &apos;t2&apos;, &apos;c&apos;, null, &apos;x&apos;);
0 rows inserted/updated/deleted
ij&amp;gt; select * from table(t2__c(&apos;abc or def&apos;, null, 3, null)) tc;
X         |DOCUMENTID |SCORE          
--------------------------------------
NULL      |NULL       |NULL           
NULL      |1          |NULL           

2 rows selected
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
