                            <comment id="14025357" author="rhillegas" created="Mon, 9 Jun 2014 18:00:44 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Attaching derby-6602-01-aa-handleNullKeys.diff. This patch adds support for null key values. The Lucene tests pass cleanly for me using this patch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There were two problems:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1) The scan of the table/view (when creating the index) wasn&apos;t checking for null values.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2) The query vti wasn&apos;t checking for null values either.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Touches the following files:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;M       java/optional/org/apache/derby/optional/lucene/LuceneQueryVTI.java&lt;br/&gt;
M       java/optional/org/apache/derby/optional/lucene/LuceneSupport.java&lt;br/&gt;
